column5: CAS  LOWER AND UPPER BOUND (Lower is > and Upper is <) Numbers within a box on top are the class, those on the bottom are bounds of the class

column17: NOTE: Shrub crown closure is included with the shrub code in NNF_ANTH, e.g. SC6 (closed shrub with 61%-70% crown closure). Shrub crown closure will need to be pulled from here and placed in the crown closure field for CAS

column14: Codes 1 to 5 used with normal cover distribution; codes 61 to 64 used with patchy vegetation distribution

column5: Assigned in 5% increments from 0 to 95%.  e.g 27% = 25, 3% = 05

column21: Must identify comercial forest vs non commercial first, then assign appropriate CC code

column5: Describes primary coverage in percentage. Codes start at 01= 1%, then, for example: 05= 5%, 35= 35%, and 00= 100%

column16: Crown closure may appear in 10% or 5% classes depending on inventory
